| Feature                     | **For-each Loop** (`for (Type var : collection)`) | **Normal For Loop** (`for (int i=0; i<n; i++)`) | **Iterator** (`Iterator<T> it = list.iterator()`) |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| **Best for**                | Simple read-only traversal                        | Index-based access, modifying by index          | Safe modification (remove/add) during iteration   |
| **Index available?**        | ‚ùå No                                              | ‚úÖ Yes (`i`)                                     | ‚ùå No                                              |
| **Can modify elements?**    | ‚ùå Not directly                                    | ‚úÖ Yes (using index)                             | ‚úÖ Yes (with `it.remove()`)                        |
| **Can remove safely?**      | ‚ùå Throws `ConcurrentModificationException`        | ‚ùå Also unsafe while looping                     | ‚úÖ Safe (using `remove()`)                         |
| **Works with arrays?**      | ‚úÖ Yes                                             | ‚úÖ Yes                                           | ‚ùå No (only collections)                           |
| **Works with collections?** | ‚úÖ Yes                                             | ‚úÖ Yes                                           | ‚úÖ Yes                                             |
| **Code simplicity**         | ‚≠ê Easiest & cleanest                              | ‚ö° Medium                                        | üõ†Ô∏è More verbose                                  |
| **Use case examples**       | Printing, searching                               | Comparing neighbors, updating array elements    | Removing items from `ArrayList` while looping     |
